Jun 2023 ‚Ä¢ Solo
A short but fairly steep walk takes you from Piazza del Popolo up to the top of Pincio. There are amazing views of Rome from the top as well as a park which contains a lot of busts of prominent Italians. There's a park which had a lot of families who were hiring go-carts, golf carts etc.

Gorgeous viewpoint
Feb 2022
We went out before sunset, walking along to the Spanish Steps and then through the Borghese Park to the far Terrazza del Pincio where we watched the sun finally sink below the horizon. The area looked like a car park but there were lots of couples and individuals just enjoying the view and/or listening to the busker. It must be fantastic to have this on your doorstep and be able to walk or run here every day.
